-- Persian Gulf Stocks: Arabtec Holding, Emaar, Sorouh Real Estate
-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 2012-03-18T13:12:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-18/persian-gulf-stocks-sorouh-real-estate-and-arabtec-holding.html
The  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  decreased for
a second day, falling 1.4 percent to 1,660.47 at the 2 p.m.
close in Dubai.  Abu Dhabi ’s  ADX General Index (ADSMI)  slipped 0.7
percent.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Arabtec Holding Co. (ARTC)   fell for a third day, losing
4.4 percent to 2.8 dirhams. The biggest publicly traded
construction company in the United Arab Emirates said it
postponed its annual general meeting to April 28 from April 5.  Emaar Properties PJSC (EMAAR)   decreased the most in more
than a week, falling 1.3 percent to 3.06 dirhams. The board of
the developer of the world’s tallest tower meets tomorrow to
discuss whether it will pay a dividend for 2011.  Sorouh Real Estate PJSC (SOROUH)   declined 6.5 percent,
the most since March 7, to 1.3 dirhams. Abu Dhabi’s second-
biggest developer said its board has elected Mubarak Matar Al Humairi as chairman.  Aldar Properties PJSC (ALDAR)  , Abu
Dhabi’s largest real-estate company which is considering a
merger with Sorouh, slumped 5 percent to 1.33 dirhams.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  